Wash and dry produce.

Drain @pineapple{4%ounce}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1};
mince a few slices until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Core, deseed,
and thinly slice @long green pepper{1} into strips. Trim root end from
@baby lettuce{1}; separate leaves.

In a #small bowl{}, combine drained pineapple, minced onion, and half the
@red wine vinegar{5%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings). Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Open package of @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} and drain off any excess
liquid. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer; cook, stirring occasionally,
until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to
a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add sliced onion
and green pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened,
~{3-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain @black beans{1}. Once veggies are slightly softened, push to
one side of pan; add beans and @BBQ sauce{4%tablespoon} to empty side. Mash half
the beans using a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until creamy.

Stir beans and veggies to combine. Add a splash of water and season with
salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until sauce has thickened and veggies are
tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Use pan used for chicken here.

Divide lettuce leaves between plates. Fill with bean filling, @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}, and pineapple salsa. Top with @crispy fried onions{1%unit}; serve.

Fill with chicken along with bean filling.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.